Preparatory Committee Inaugurated in Romania 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Romanian Preparatory Committee for Commemorating the Day of the Sun and Celebrating Feb. 16 was held at the building of the Socialist Party of Romania on Jan 9.
 Speakers at the ceremony said that they would organize colorful functions on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il this year, too. Availing themselves of this opportunity, they said, they would make a deep study of the originality of the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il and the advantages of Korean-style socialism and extend positive support and solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle for independent and peaceful reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vasile Orleanu, chairman of the Supreme Council of the Romanian Socialist Party and chairman of the Romanian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee set a period of commemoration and celebration from Jan. 10 to Apr. 15 and decided to organize colorful functions including meeting, seminar, lecture, film show and photo exhibition in the period.

KCTU Checks U.S. Ambassador's Round-table Conversation with Journalists 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions (KCTU) checked a round-table conversation with journalists of the U.S. ambassador in Seoul on Jan. 12, according to the south Korean KBS.
 The U.S. ambassador was scheduled to have a round-table conversation with Internet journalists at the building of the south Korean Internet Journalists' Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KCTU castigated the U.S. ambassador for making reckless remarks slandering the north as a "criminal regime" and strongly opposed his call on the association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He could not appear in the venue owing to the fierce protest of the KCTU and had to give up his schedule.

U.S. Chiefly Accountable for Having Totally Scrapped DPRK-U.S. Agreed Framework 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- The United States can never evade its responsibility for having totally scrapped the DPRK-U.S. Agreed Framework (AF) and delayed the settlement of the nuclear issue in a deliberate manner.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday observes this in a signed commentary. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some officials are spreading misinformation that the DPRK is to blame for the end of the unsuccessful construction of the light water reactors (LWRs), while demanding it "compensate" for this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main spirit of the AF called on both sides to respect each other's sovereignty and create reconciliation and trust in order to put an end to the hostile relations between them and, furthermore, ensure peace and security in the Korean Peninsula and other parts of Asia-Pacific and the rest of the world.
 The LWR project, a key point of the AF, was considered to be a guarantee for terminating the hostile relations between the DPRK and the U.S. and finding a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula. Under the AF the U.S. was committed to providing two LWRs to the DPRK by the year 2003 in return for the latter's freeze of nuclear facilities and supplying 500,000 tons of heavy fuel oil to it every year till their construction is completed. The U.S. also gave the DPRK assurances that it would not threaten the latter with nukes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., however, has not fulfilled any commitment under the AF. The Bush administration categorically refused to implement the AF and has systematically perpetrated premeditated acts of totally scrapping official documents signed between the DPRK and the U.S., unreasonably asserting that a series of agreements including the AF signed by the preceding regime with the DPRK are "beneficial" to it only, while being harmful to the U.S. interests and prestige. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite nonsensical for some politicians to urge the DPRK to "compensate" for the unsuccessful end of the LWR construction in stead of holding the U.S. chiefly accountable for the abrogation of the AF. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the DPRK that has to claim compensation for the loss caused by the suspension of the LWR project. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whoever is concerned about the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula should properly know who stands for the denuclearization of the peninsula and who persistently blocks it.

Rodong Sinmun on Revolutionary Line and Policies of WPK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- The line and policies of the Workers' Party of Korea for building a great prosperous powerful nation serve as a banner of sure victory based on the Songun idea of Juche. 
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a by-lined article today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun idea of Juche crystallizes the fundamental principles of the Korean revolution which was pioneered by arms and has emerged victorious and the precious guidelines of party, state and army building in the Songun era and indicates a straight shortcut to social transformation, nature remaking and human remoulding in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea serves as a starting point, a basic cornerstone of all the line and policies of the Party in the Songun era. The line and policies strengthening the revolutionary army into an invincible army and making revolutionary ranks an elite one with it as the main force, giving priority to the development of national defence industry while simultaneously developing light industry and agriculture and opening a new history of Songun revolutionary culture are the banner of struggle guaranteeing a victorious advance for building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the staunch policy and stand of the Party to counter the aggressive moves of the U.S. imperialists and reactionaries with a merciless military strike, their vicious offensive to isolate and stifle the DPRK with revolutionary economic strategy and their despicable psychological warfare with a powerful ideological battle. The policy and stand instill the conviction of victory into the army and people of Korea all out in building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The line and policies of the Party for building a great prosperous powerful nation serve as an invincible weapon based on the revolutionary zeal and creative power of the army and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the great pride of the Party to have such army and people who have unchangeable confidence in the justness and victory of the socialist cause, revolutionary optimism that they break through trials, always cheerful although their path is thorny and the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance that they create something out of nothing and faith can move even a mountain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The signal successes in all fields of politics, military affairs, economy and culture and the might of the DPRK as a powerful country of Songun clearly prove how just and viable the revolutionary line and policies of the Party are, the article concludes.

National Seminar Held on Exploits Performed by Three Generals in Leadership over Youth Movement 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on the exploits performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu in the leadership over the youth movement took place at the April 25 House of Culture Monday on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League. 
 Presented at the seminar were six papers that made a profound scientific and theoretical explanation of the undying leadership exploits performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu in pioneering, strengthening and developing the Korean youth movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floor was taken by Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter Kim Ok Sun, Kim Jong Suk, editor-in-chief of Minju Joson, Kim Yong Sik, first secretary of the Committee of the Korean People's Army of the Youth League, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the seminar noted that President Kim Il Sung who established the glorious tradition of the Juche-oriented youth movement in the period of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle laid down the line of building the popular and monolithic youth organization even under so difficult and complicated situation right after the liberation of Korea and proclaimed the foundation of the Democratic Youth League to the world on January 17, Juche 35 (1946). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that Kim Il Sung gave a genuine origin to the Juche-oriented youth movement, set an example of world historic significance in building revolutionary youth organizations and strengthened and developed the youth league to be an organization intensely loyal to the Party and the revolutionary cause, they stressed that his revolutionary exploits would  shine forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They explained the immortal leadership feats Kim Jong Il has performed by putting up the slogan "Love the Youth!" and placing the work of the youth league on a new higher stage as required by the developing revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that Kim Jong Il was the first in history to formulate the idea and theory of the youth movement based on the revolutionary outlook on the leader, they noted that he made sure that the youth league was renamed the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League and has strengthened and developed it into the youth organization of the President, the reliable ranks of members of the young vanguard of Songun by providing wise leadership and showing profound care for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The path of victory and glory covered by the youth league is closely associated with the undying exploits performed by anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk who performed distinguished feats in establishing the glorious revolutionary tradition of the Korean youth movement and energetically led the work of the youth league after liberation, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the officials of the youth league and other young people to resolutely uphold and glorify the undying exploits performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu in developing the Korean youth movement and accomplish generation after generation the revolutionary cause of Juche that started in the Paektu forest, true to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the seminar were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, participants in the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the youth league and members of the delegation of Korean youths and students in Japan and the delegation of the Youth Federation of Korean Nationals in China.

Kim Jong Il's Leadership, Key to Victory
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- The servicepersons and the people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are steadfastly advancing along one road of revolution, overcoming every manner of trials and hardships.
 The seasoned leadership of Kim Jong Il guarantees that the Korean revolution has emerged victorious without any slightest vacillation, going through the storm and stress of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung, in his lifetime, said with conviction that Kim Jong Il was the symbol and the future of Juche Korea and the revolutionary cause of Juche would win victory after victory under his guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His great Songun idea lighting the way for realizing the independence of the popular masses, extraordinary commanding art making it possible to defeat any formidable enemy and the creative power turning impossibility to possibility and creating thing out of nothing are the source of victory for the Korean army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last ten-odd year history of Songun revolution is brilliantly adorned with the tested leadership of Kim Jong Il, who has wrought world-startling miracles through thick and thin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has developed in depth the Songun idea fathered by the President to be a mode of politics in our era, thus providing the army and people with the valuable sword of certain victory with which they can firmly defend the socialist fatherland from the imperialist enemies and push ahead with the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is thanks to his Songun idea and politics that the DPRK has successfully stood against the outrageous nuclear blackmail of the imperialists and turned into an impregnable fortress with strong self-defensive nuclear deterrent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With his outstanding leadership he met enemies' hard-line with super one and always drove them into the defensive, winning victory after victory.
 Under his leadership hundreds of thousands of hectares of arable land were rezoned to suit the features of the socialist country, totally eliminating the centuries-long feudal remnants. And monumental edifices including the Taean Friendship Glass Factory and Paekma-Cholsan Waterway have been built in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, last year witnessed greater successes than those in the recent few years in the field of economic construction. This eloquently proves the fact that the realization of his intention of building a great prosperous powerful nation is not a matter of the distant future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK, who have laid a solid foundation for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and won only victory under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il, took a big step toward greater victory this year.
